      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 128: reset() does not cancel the active progressive zoom animator. When pinch-to-zoom is disabled or the view is reconfigured while a long-press zoom is running, the animator can continue applying transforms to the TextureView after reset/detach, causing unexpected zoom state and retaining the view longer than needed. Stop the animator before clearing state.\n```suggestion\nfun reset() {\n    stopProgressiveZoom()\n    scale \u003d 1f\n    translateX \u003d 0f\n    translateY \u003d 0f\n    apply()\n}\n```",
