      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 139: The attached touch listener always returns true, even for a simple single-finger tap/drag when the view is not zoomed. Since ParticipantsContainerView enables this on active participant sinks, this can consume touch events that previously reached parent views or click handlers. Return true only when the helper actually handles a zoom/pan gesture, and let normal taps propagate otherwise.\n```suggestion\nval handled \u003d scaleDetector.isInProgress || ev.pointerCount \u003e 1 || scale \u003e minScale\nwhen (ev.actionMasked) {\n    MotionEvent.ACTION_UP -\u003e {\n        stopProgressiveZoom()\n        if (!handled) v.performClick()\n    }\n    MotionEvent.ACTION_CANCEL,\n    MotionEvent.ACTION_POINTER_DOWN -\u003e stopProgressiveZoom()\n}\nhandled\n```",
